Filtering Methods
A total of 366 rows were removed because sequencing was performed using whole genome shotgun (WGS) rather than 16S rRNA as indicated under the “Assay Type” column
An additional 123 rows corresponding to blank samples were excluded based on entries in the host_subject_id or name_sample columns
To avoid disproportionate effects from participants sampled at multiple timepoints, only the first visit was retained for each individual
-  In total, 338 samples representing non-first visits were removed
-    duplicates were identified using host_subject_id
-    the earliest timepoint was retained based on the Collection_Date column
-  For 11 duplicates, the collection dates were unavailable
-    instead, age was used to infer the earliest sample (younger age indicating an earlier timepoint)
-  In cases where age data were also missing or identical across visits
-    sample IDs were used as a proxy, as they are typically assigned in chronological order#

Four samples were excluded due to unsuccessful sequencing runs
  characterized by abnormally short read lengths and the presence of higher-quality duplicates collected on the same day

12 samples with no available metadata (all fields missing/NA) were removed

After these filtering steps, 572 samples remained for downstream analysis
